      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROCKET RALPH (7) had about the mark in recent times before turning things around at his latest appearance over 1720m at this track, scoring by 4.5 metres after being on the pace throughout. Drawn to enjoy a nice run, with luck possibly playing a role at some point. Has the class to make it back-to-back wins. SO CAN EYE (1) did a decent job from a tough barrier last start. Should get every chance from the ace draw. FOR SIXES (8) opened his career in the best possible manner last start, scoring by 1.3 metres over 1740m at Riverina Paceway. Drawn to enjoy a cosy run but might need things to go his way at some stage. Meets a comparable field and he can salute once again. WICKED WHISKEY (4) last appeared when he got home by 4 metres over 1780m at Redcliffe five months ago. Should be thereabouts.",
